storyText: Thomas got to Annika’s Finer Diner early, dreading the conversation he was about to have.
The restaurant had a kitschy charm and was reminiscent of a diner from the 70’s.
A bell chimed as the door swung open, and Sadie entered to find him deep in thought on a bench by the door.
The grocery store was not the place Emmanuella and Liam wanted to be as they had been fighting beforehand, to the point where Emmanuella was thinking of breaking up with Liam.
